A vintage-style illustration depicting the journey of a letter through an elaborate mechanical sorting system, shown as a cross-section view of a grand postal facility. The letter travels along brass tubes, conveyor belts, and pneumatic chutes, passing through various ornate checkpoints with gears, stamps, and inspection stations. Each station features intricate Victorian-era machinery with gauges and levers examining the envelope. The color palette uses warm sepia tones, aged paper textures, and copper metallics. The perspective shows the complete path from entry to delivery, with the letter glowing subtly as it moves through each processing stage, suggesting transformation and scrutiny at every step.
